# App environment variables — THE REGISTRY, not the values.
#
# How this works:
# - Need an API key or setting (OpenAI, Google Maps, Stripe, …)? Add a
#   line here with the value BLANK plus a short comment, commit + push:
#
#     OPENAI_API_KEY=BLANK  # powers the AI summaries on the dashboard
#
# - The user sees every line of this file in the Environment tab, fills
#   in the real value, and saves. Values go straight to the Vercel
#   project env (production + preview targets) and both branches
#   redeploy — they are NEVER committed to this repo. You'll be woken
#   when a value lands.
# - In app code, read the variable normally: process.env.OPENAI_API_KEY
#   (server-side; NEXT_PUBLIC_ prefix only for values that are safe to
#   ship to the browser).
#
# NEVER write a real secret value into this file.
